More Neighborhood Flash Mob pictures!

post_text:
Mancho Gonzalez, Taylor's Music teacher, organized an event he called "Neighborhood Flash Mob". The event took
place on Friday April 17th where music students were asked
to go out to the front of their house/apartment and play 3-5
songs for the neighbors. Drummers could play some beats on buckets turned upside down. Taylor and District staff
carovanned around the neighborhoods to hear and see some of the action!

post_text: Green Hills Elementary 3rd Grade teacher, Cezanne Flowers, won a grant for her school from the "Step up to the Plate for Education" program developed by San Francisco Giant's All-Star shortstop, Brandon Crawford in association with Wells Fargo and KNBR! Through an open community nomination process, the grant program disbursed a total of $100,000 to support athletics, arts, STEAM and community-based programs. The award was spread among 28 Bay Area schools. Congrats to Cezanne and to Green Hills Elementary School! Nice work!
